The <b>IBM 805 Test Scoring Machine</b> was a machine sold by IBM beginning in 1937.  The device scored answer sheets marked with special "<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../142/2363142.xml">
mark sense</link>" pencils.  The machine was developed from a prototype developed by <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
